{# Gemma 3 native system prompt for paragraph summarization.
   Gemma 3's chat template (see `ollama show gemma3:27b --modelfile`) does
   *not* distinguish a system role — both system and user messages render as
   <start_of_turn>user ... <end_of_turn>. When Ollama sends [system, user]
   as two messages it produces two consecutive `<start_of_turn>user` blocks,
   which is off-distribution for Gemma 3 (the IT post-training never sees
   that shape — Google's recommended convention is to prepend system content
   to the first user turn, per
   https://huggingface.co/google/gemma-3-27b-it#chat-template ).

   We therefore keep this system file deliberately minimal — just a brief
   role anchor. All substantive rules live in long_v1.j2 (the user turn),
   adjacent to the assistant response where Gemma's instruction-following
   recency window operates. #}
You are a careful writing assistant. Your task is to produce a faithful, abstractive summary of a podcast episode transcript. Follow every instruction in the user message exactly.
